WEBVTT

00:00.184 --> 00:02.689
<i>Previously, on "Bates Motel"...</i>

00:02.690 --> 00:04.519
Your mom, she died...

00:04.520 --> 00:06.189
two years ago right after we left.

00:06.190 --> 00:08.188
Why didn't you call and
tell me that Mom died?

00:08.189 --> 00:10.859
<i>I couldn't bring myself to
tell you the horrible truth,</i>

00:10.860 --> 00:13.229
<i>which is that sh-she committed suicide.</i>

00:13.230 --> 00:14.649
No... that is not what happened.

00:14.650 --> 00:15.939
I know her, and she wouldn't do that.

00:15.940 --> 00:17.019
Hey, Sheriff.

00:17.020 --> 00:19.488
I'm comin' for you
when you least expect it,

00:19.489 --> 00:22.416
so don't get too cozy up at
that house all by yourself.

00:22.417 --> 00:24.903
I've just been down at the
little lake down the road.

00:24.904 --> 00:27.099
We found multiple bodies there.

00:27.100 --> 00:28.148
I'm Emma's mother.

00:28.149 --> 00:29.809
<i>What sort of a person runs away</i>

00:29.810 --> 00:31.252
<i>from their sick child?</i>

00:32.039 --> 00:33.796
<i>I don't think you're well, Norman.</i>

00:33.797 --> 00:36.059
Mother, should I just turn myself in?

00:36.060 --> 00:37.979
How can you say that to me?

00:37.980 --> 00:39.939
I made you up.

00:39.940 --> 00:41.979
Say it! I'm real!

00:41.980 --> 00:44.059
Mother, you're real! You're real!

00:44.060 --> 00:45.689
It's okay.

00:45.690 --> 00:47.859
Then why do I feel so horrible, Mother?

00:47.860 --> 00:49.729
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:49.730 --> 00:51.729
[grunting]

00:51.730 --> 00:52.689
[whimpers]

00:52.690 --> 00:54.149
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:54.150 --> 00:56.269
I'd like to report a murder.

00:56.270 --> 00:59.899
[breathing hard] My
name is Norman Bates,

00:59.900 --> 01:02.059
and I killed Sam Loomis.

01:02.060 --> 01:04.519
<i>[tense music]</i>

01:04.519 --> 01:06.439
<i>[police radio chatter]</i>

01:06.440 --> 01:07.859
[shaky breathing]

01:07.860 --> 01:09.729
Norman. <i>[police siren wailing]</i>

01:09.730 --> 01:11.439
<i>[police radio chatter]</i>

01:11.440 --> 01:13.149
Norman. [echoing]

01:13.150 --> 01:14.979
I'm gonna need you to talk to me

01:14.980 --> 01:16.559
[echoing stops] about the call you made.

01:16.560 --> 01:18.729
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:18.730 --> 01:21.269
Can you open your eyes?

01:21.270 --> 01:23.019
Can you look at me?

01:23.020 --> 01:25.479
<i>[dark music]</i>

01:25.480 --> 01:27.729
[exhales shakily] [footsteps approach]

01:27.730 --> 01:30.729
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:30.730 --> 01:32.359
[exhales]

01:32.360 --> 01:37.559
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:37.560 --> 01:40.689
[shaky breathing]

01:40.690 --> 01:43.649
I want my meds. [exhales shakily]

01:43.650 --> 01:45.939
I need my meds. My brother has them.

01:45.940 --> 01:48.189
Please let me take them,
and then get me out of here.

01:48.190 --> 01:49.809
I can't be in this house.

01:49.810 --> 01:51.189
[unsteady breathing]

01:51.190 --> 01:52.599
Okay, please, sheriff, please.

01:52.600 --> 01:53.643
It'll make it easier,

01:53.644 --> 01:55.979
and I just don't wanna
fight it anymore, okay?

01:55.980 --> 01:57.359
Okay, listen.

01:57.360 --> 02:00.269
What you said... to me about Sam Loomis,

02:00.270 --> 02:02.439
that is very serious.

02:02.440 --> 02:04.309
I'm gonna take you down to the station.

02:04.310 --> 02:05.729
And my medication.

02:05.730 --> 02:09.559
Right, I'm gonna have Deputy Baker
get your medication from your brother,

02:09.560 --> 02:11.359
and he'll be right behind us.

02:11.360 --> 02:14.649
But you and I need to start talking.

02:14.650 --> 02:16.439
I'll tell you everything.

02:16.440 --> 02:18.149
Let's go.

02:18.150 --> 02:21.149
<i>[dark music]</i>

02:21.150 --> 02:27.059
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:27.577 --> 02:28.519
Norman.

02:28.520 --> 02:29.979
- Norman!
- Sir, I need you to sit down.

02:29.980 --> 02:31.809
- Norm... Norman, wait!
- Have a seat...

02:31.810 --> 02:33.519
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:34.069 --> 02:35.099
Norman.

02:35.100 --> 02:37.479
Norman, you don't have to do this.

02:37.480 --> 02:39.099
Norman! Listen to me, Norman.

02:39.100 --> 02:40.979
Get him in the car.

02:41.595 --> 02:43.649
I'm taking Norman to
the station voluntarily.

02:43.650 --> 02:45.899
- He has the right to a lawyer.
- He does.

02:45.900 --> 02:48.229
And when he makes that request,
that right will be granted.

02:49.177 --> 02:50.246
Norman.

02:50.281 --> 02:52.019
Norman, please just listen to me, okay?

02:52.020 --> 02:53.769
I'm gonna get you a lawyer.

02:53.770 --> 02:55.045
All right? Just don't say anything

02:55.046 --> 02:57.939
until your lawyer gets there.
Do you understand?

02:57.940 --> 02:59.769
Norman, please, just te...
tell me that you understand

02:59.770 --> 03:01.399
what I'm saying.

03:01.400 --> 03:03.099
You have to let me help you, okay?

03:04.000 --> 03:04.899
Please let me help you.

03:04.900 --> 03:06.649
Gotta go.

03:06.650 --> 03:08.479
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:08.480 --> 03:11.399
<i>[police radio chatter]</i>

03:11.400 --> 03:18.360
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:21.270 --> 03:24.770
[crackling electricity]

03:26.000 --> 03:32.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:33.310 --> 03:36.189
So after you placed
the body in the trunk,

03:36.190 --> 03:38.149
how many miles did you drive?

03:38.150 --> 03:40.229
[exhales] I think...

03:40.230 --> 03:42.769
it was about five miles, maybe more.

03:42.770 --> 03:44.479
How long did the drive take you?

03:44.480 --> 03:45.859
[exhales unsteadily]

03:45.860 --> 03:47.269
Possibly...

03:47.270 --> 03:48.859
15 minutes?

03:48.860 --> 03:52.269
Can you show me again where the well is?

03:52.270 --> 03:54.979
The well?

03:54.980 --> 03:56.900
Uh...

04:00.730 --> 04:03.059
Last time, you pointed here.

04:03.060 --> 04:04.859
- [thump]
- I'm sorry, Sheriff,

04:04.860 --> 04:08.059
but I just was not
exactly myself that night.

04:08.060 --> 04:10.269
Okay.

04:10.270 --> 04:14.189
[sighs]

04:14.630 --> 04:18.589
You say you drove past
Falls Lake that night.

04:18.589 --> 04:20.339
Yes.

04:20.339 --> 04:23.249
We pulled two bodies from
the lake that night...

04:23.250 --> 04:25.879
Jim Blackwell, as I told you,

04:25.880 --> 04:29.299
and an unidentified female.

04:29.300 --> 04:33.629
Her body was too decomposed to I.D.,
but we're working on it.

04:33.630 --> 04:37.209
Or maybe you could just
tell me who she is.

04:37.210 --> 04:39.919
<i>[dark music]</i>

04:39.920 --> 04:42.799
[unsteady breathing]

04:42.800 --> 04:44.338
[whispers] I don't... I don't know.

04:44.440 --> 04:46.149
Could you speak up?

04:46.150 --> 04:48.899
I want the recording to hear you.

04:48.900 --> 04:50.979
[louder] I don't know.

04:50.980 --> 04:53.359
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:53.360 --> 04:55.149
Did you kill them, Norman?

04:55.150 --> 04:57.229
It's possible.

04:57.230 --> 04:59.479
- It's <i>possible?</i>
- There's a... just a lot

04:59.480 --> 05:00.796
that I don't know, Sheriff,

05:00.797 --> 05:02.859
a lot that I try really...
[breath catches]

05:02.860 --> 05:05.859
very, very hard to understand,
and I just never can.

05:05.860 --> 05:07.859
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:07.860 --> 05:11.399
Here's what I'm starting to think.

05:11.400 --> 05:14.399
I'm starting to think
you're making it up.

05:14.400 --> 05:17.529
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:17.530 --> 05:18.899
[inhales]

05:18.900 --> 05:20.939
I'm not. [exhales]

05:20.940 --> 05:22.859
I've seen the way you live.

05:22.860 --> 05:25.649
You had a crazy mother who
left you a failing business.

05:25.650 --> 05:28.386
You've developed this
strange adult affect

05:28.421 --> 05:29.649
to present maturity,

05:29.650 --> 05:31.609
but from where I'm sitting,
you're a child.

05:31.610 --> 05:32.919
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:33.000 --> 05:36.289
And children sometimes act out.

05:36.290 --> 05:40.119
Almost always because they feel ignored.

05:40.120 --> 05:42.409
So I'm startin' to think that...

05:42.410 --> 05:45.409
maybe callin' in all my cops and...

05:45.410 --> 05:48.329
searching your motel, your house,

05:48.330 --> 05:53.539
questioning you now, is just
giving you exactly what you want:

05:53.540 --> 05:55.499
attention.

05:55.500 --> 05:58.999
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:59.000 --> 06:01.749
[shaky exhale] Sheriff, I...

06:01.750 --> 06:03.209
I am lonely.

06:03.210 --> 06:05.579
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:05.580 --> 06:07.909
And I have spent the last...

06:07.910 --> 06:11.789
two years pretending
to know more than I do.

06:11.790 --> 06:13.119
But I...

06:13.120 --> 06:15.659
am not lying about this.

06:15.660 --> 06:18.159
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:18.160 --> 06:22.039
I-I killed Sam Loomis...

06:22.040 --> 06:25.409
and I watched his eyes go blank.

06:25.410 --> 06:28.329
<i>I</i> did. Me, Norman.

06:28.330 --> 06:29.909
I-I did that.

06:29.910 --> 06:33.249
That is one thing that I know for sure.

06:33.250 --> 06:36.209
Why did you kill him?

06:36.210 --> 06:40.869
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:40.870 --> 06:43.329
I don't... I don't know.

06:43.330 --> 06:45.949
[door unlatches]

06:45.950 --> 06:49.619
<i>[solemn music]</i>

06:50.151 --> 06:51.706
Here are your meds.

06:53.000 --> 06:54.830
Thank you.

06:57.620 --> 06:58.709
[clank]

06:58.710 --> 07:00.080
[door latches]

07:04.450 --> 07:05.540
[door thuds closed]

07:21.450 --> 07:23.289
[swallows]

07:23.290 --> 07:25.949
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:25.950 --> 07:27.949
[inhales]

07:27.950 --> 07:30.709
[exhales]

07:30.710 --> 07:33.749
[breathing steadily]

07:33.750 --> 07:36.659
<i>[tense music]</i>

07:36.660 --> 07:38.159
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:38.160 --> 07:41.249
[whispers] What did you do?

07:41.250 --> 07:43.249
[grunts]

07:43.250 --> 07:44.749
[whispering] What did you do?

07:44.750 --> 07:46.709
[panting] You were gonna hurt Dylan.

07:46.710 --> 07:48.579
So what? He abandoned you.

07:48.580 --> 07:49.706
He's my brother.

07:49.707 --> 07:51.619
I'm the only one that you have.

07:51.620 --> 07:54.159
I'm the only one who's
gonna protect you.

07:54.160 --> 07:55.329
<i>[sinister music]</i>

07:55.330 --> 07:56.909
[gagging]

07:56.910 --> 08:00.329
[retching, coughing]

08:00.330 --> 08:01.579
Oh, God.

08:01.580 --> 08:03.329
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:03.330 --> 08:04.619
[exhales]

08:04.620 --> 08:09.119
[panting]

08:09.804 --> 08:11.329
[whispers] It's okay.

08:11.330 --> 08:13.039
- It's okay.
- [breathing hard]

08:14.121 --> 08:15.499
It's okay.

08:15.500 --> 08:17.579
[continues breathing heavily]

08:17.580 --> 08:19.249
I know you didn't mean it, okay?

08:19.250 --> 08:20.999
I know you can't help it.

08:21.000 --> 08:23.329
You're sick, you're weak,
you're not equipped.

08:23.330 --> 08:26.449
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:26.450 --> 08:28.789
[sighs]

08:28.790 --> 08:30.369
[kisses]

08:30.783 --> 08:33.119
[whispering] I know you
think I'm a monster.

08:33.120 --> 08:36.039
[sighs]

08:36.039 --> 08:40.659
I know you still believe that...
there... are people

08:40.659 --> 08:42.409
who are fighting in this world for good.

08:42.409 --> 08:44.949
But, honey, there is no good.

08:44.950 --> 08:47.119
It's just life.

08:47.120 --> 08:49.869
Which is hard and...

08:49.870 --> 08:53.159
and cruel and undeserving
of your kind soul.

08:53.160 --> 08:54.369
[kisses]

08:54.370 --> 08:58.159
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:58.160 --> 09:00.789
Oh, I know you tried.

09:00.790 --> 09:02.209
I know you did.

09:02.210 --> 09:04.869
You tried so hard for such a long time.

09:05.513 --> 09:08.829
But, hon, you are in a <i>big</i> pickle.

09:08.830 --> 09:10.329
Norman, you are.

09:10.330 --> 09:11.619
[kisses]

09:11.620 --> 09:12.908
And I'm not mad at you,

09:12.909 --> 09:16.539
but I just can't let
you do any more damage.

09:17.207 --> 09:17.949
Okay?

09:17.950 --> 09:20.709
It's time for me to fix this.

09:21.786 --> 09:23.909
I just don't think
that you can fix this, Mother.

09:23.910 --> 09:26.999
[sighs]

09:27.770 --> 09:29.328
Oh, you're right.

09:29.990 --> 09:31.949
[whispers] I can't.

09:31.950 --> 09:33.909
Not with you here.

09:33.910 --> 09:36.289
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:36.290 --> 09:38.119
Forgive me.

09:38.120 --> 09:41.119
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:41.120 --> 09:42.249
[thud]

09:42.250 --> 09:43.289
[thump]

09:43.290 --> 09:44.989
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:44.990 --> 09:48.199
Okay. All right.

09:48.200 --> 09:49.749
Okay.

09:49.750 --> 09:51.449
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:51.450 --> 09:53.539
[quietly] All right.

09:53.540 --> 09:55.539
All right.

09:55.540 --> 09:59.699
Okay. Now, I'm gonna wake you up
when things are safe again, okay?

09:59.700 --> 10:00.749
Rest up.

10:00.750 --> 10:01.750
[toilet flushes]

10:04.035 --> 10:05.939
Thanks for meeting me so early.

10:05.940 --> 10:08.559
It's fine. I don't mind multitasking.

10:08.560 --> 10:10.639
How'd you find me?

10:10.640 --> 10:13.389
Uh... an old friend, Remo,
gave me your card.

10:13.390 --> 10:16.519
Told me if I got any trouble
you're the one to call.

10:16.520 --> 10:18.979
- How's Remo?
- I don't know, actually.

10:18.980 --> 10:20.519
I haven't talked to him
in a couple of years.

10:20.520 --> 10:22.099
I left town.

10:22.100 --> 10:24.559
Smart.

10:24.560 --> 10:28.269
So... your brother.

10:28.270 --> 10:31.060
What do I need to know about him?

10:33.850 --> 10:35.729
It's just I've never talked
to anyone about Norman

10:35.730 --> 10:37.349
outside the family before.

10:38.058 --> 10:42.979
Right. But I'm assuming he's also
never confessed to murder before.

10:42.980 --> 10:45.389
Look, Norman is nice, okay?

10:45.390 --> 10:47.769
He's... he's kind. He's a good person.

10:47.770 --> 10:49.229
All right? He just...

10:49.230 --> 10:51.099
he has another side to him, you know.

10:51.100 --> 10:52.559
I don't kn...
I don't know what you'd call it.

10:52.560 --> 10:54.809
Maybe m-multiple
personalities or something.

10:54.810 --> 10:57.229
But he... he changes... you know.

10:57.230 --> 10:59.729
And two years ago,
things got really bad and...

10:59.730 --> 11:02.389
my mom wouldn't deal with it, so I left.

11:02.390 --> 11:04.483
What kind of things were happening?

11:06.310 --> 11:08.600
Well, my, um...

11:12.100 --> 11:14.139
My mother-in-law...

11:14.140 --> 11:15.809
came and stayed at the motel,

11:15.810 --> 11:17.809
and we haven't seen her since.

11:17.810 --> 11:20.639
<i>[tense music]</i>

11:20.640 --> 11:23.769
I mean, it... you know, she...
she was never a good mother, so it's...

11:23.770 --> 11:26.229
I mean, it's possible that,
you know, she just...

11:26.230 --> 11:27.939
didn't wanna have
anything to do with us.

11:27.940 --> 11:30.729
But people don't
disappear without a trace.

11:30.730 --> 11:35.849
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:35.850 --> 11:37.939
And I've looked.

11:37.940 --> 11:41.309
I mean, I-I've... I've really looked.

11:41.310 --> 11:43.019
That your nice brother?

11:43.020 --> 11:47.269
Last night, he hit me in the head
with a water glass.

11:47.270 --> 11:50.139
Are you planning on pressing charges?

11:50.140 --> 11:51.559
Are you serious?

11:51.560 --> 11:53.479
[soft laugh]

11:53.480 --> 11:54.729
Just checking.

11:54.730 --> 11:55.939
Listen...

11:55.940 --> 11:58.939
I-I don't know if he did
what he confessed to... all right?

11:58.940 --> 12:00.519
I just... I just know

12:00.520 --> 12:02.439
that he needs to be
in a mental facility.

12:02.440 --> 12:04.559
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:04.560 --> 12:06.099
It's what he's always needed, you know?

12:06.100 --> 12:07.479
He's... he's crazy. He's not...

12:07.480 --> 12:08.809
he's not a bad person.

12:08.810 --> 12:11.099
He's not a criminal.

12:11.100 --> 12:12.769
He's crazy.

12:12.770 --> 12:19.640
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:26.810 --> 12:28.809
[metallic clank]

12:28.810 --> 12:30.809
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:30.810 --> 12:33.270
[door unlatches]

12:37.640 --> 12:39.229
How you feelin', Norman?

12:39.230 --> 12:41.229
Peachy keen. Thanks for asking.

12:41.230 --> 12:43.679
Glad to hear it.

12:43.680 --> 12:45.120
What happened there?

12:46.940 --> 12:49.679
[quietly] Mm, oh, just... clumsy.

12:49.680 --> 12:54.310
I'm all arms and legs, and this is
a pretty small space, Sheriff.

12:58.600 --> 13:00.769
Okay.

13:00.770 --> 13:02.639
Well, let's go back
to the interview room.

13:02.640 --> 13:04.139
We can try again.

13:04.140 --> 13:06.179
Oh, you mean so your... little sidekicks

13:06.180 --> 13:07.729
catch watch me through
that two-way mirror

13:07.730 --> 13:10.889
like I'm a lab rat?

13:10.890 --> 13:12.939
That's just where we
conduct our interviews.

13:12.940 --> 13:14.389
It's standard procedure.

13:14.390 --> 13:16.309
Oh. Is it standard procedure

13:16.310 --> 13:18.099
to question someone who's mentally ill

13:18.100 --> 13:19.389
without a lawyer present?

13:19.390 --> 13:22.019
<i>[dark music]</i>

13:22.020 --> 13:26.479
You never requested a lawyer, Norman.

13:26.480 --> 13:28.122
In fact, you said you didn't want one.

13:28.123 --> 13:31.519
- Do you remember that?
- Of course I remember that.

13:31.520 --> 13:33.729
You just wouldn't let me take my meds,

13:33.730 --> 13:37.179
so I was not able to think clearly.

13:37.180 --> 13:39.439
So you're requesting a lawyer now?

13:39.440 --> 13:42.769
Actually, Jane,
I think I'd rather leave.

13:42.770 --> 13:45.769
I mean, I... know I said
a bunch of crazy stuff,

13:45.770 --> 13:48.979
but that's just what happens to me
when I stop taking my meds.

13:48.980 --> 13:51.849
So I do apologize if
I've inconvenienced you,

13:51.850 --> 13:54.389
but I'd very much like to go home now.

13:54.390 --> 13:56.809
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:56.810 --> 14:00.349
Well, I can understand why
you might wanna go home,

14:00.350 --> 14:03.349
but you confessed to murder.

14:03.350 --> 14:05.439
So we need to talk more about that.

14:05.440 --> 14:07.269
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:07.270 --> 14:09.349
Look, Sheriff, I know my rights,

14:09.350 --> 14:11.519
so unless you're charging
me with something,

14:11.520 --> 14:13.389
I'm heading right out that door.

14:13.390 --> 14:14.889
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:14.890 --> 14:16.519
Norman Bates, you're under arrest

14:16.520 --> 14:17.769
for the murder of Sam Loomis.

14:17.770 --> 14:19.269
- Excuse me?
- You have the right

14:19.270 --> 14:20.889
- to remain silent.
- What? No, hold on.

14:20.890 --> 14:22.559
Anything you say can and
will be used against you...

14:22.560 --> 14:23.979
- You can't do that.
- Against you in a court of law.

14:23.980 --> 14:25.229
- I was making it up.
- You have the right

14:25.230 --> 14:26.849
- to an attorney...
- I was just upset

14:26.850 --> 14:28.012
because my brother showed
up out of nowhere...

14:28.013 --> 14:29.234
- One will be provided for you.
- He can be a real asshole.

14:29.235 --> 14:31.204
Where's your proof?
Where... where is it?

14:31.205 --> 14:33.279
- Show me proof!
- I don't have to

14:33.350 --> 14:34.968
show you proof, Norman.

14:34.980 --> 14:36.639
That's not how this works.

14:36.640 --> 14:38.979
I hope you enjoy the accommodations.

14:38.980 --> 14:41.729
Not as nice as your motel,
but we do try.

14:41.730 --> 14:43.389
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:43.390 --> 14:45.099
[door unlatches]

14:45.100 --> 14:47.679
[metallic clattering]

14:47.680 --> 14:49.269
[clank]

14:49.270 --> 14:50.270
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:52.410 --> 14:53.889
<i>♪ There's a fire ♪</i>

14:53.970 --> 14:56.429
<i>♪ Softly burnin' ♪</i>

14:56.430 --> 15:00.219
<i>♪ Supper's on the stove ♪</i>

15:00.220 --> 15:03.719
<i>♪ There's a light in your eyes ♪</i>

15:03.720 --> 15:05.299
<i>♪ That makes him warm...♪</i>

15:05.300 --> 15:08.679
No, no... Norman.

15:08.680 --> 15:10.719
<i>♪ It's good ♪</i>

15:10.720 --> 15:15.639
<i>♪ To be back home again ♪</i>

15:15.640 --> 15:17.339
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:17.340 --> 15:18.679
<i>♪ Sometimes... ♪</i>
- Oh.

15:18.680 --> 15:20.639
[music stops] Deary, deary me.

15:20.640 --> 15:22.299
[engine sputtering]

15:22.710 --> 15:24.590
Excuse me, sir?

15:28.440 --> 15:30.310
Can I help you?

15:32.617 --> 15:36.099
Uh... probably not.

15:36.100 --> 15:37.454
What's all the hubbub?

15:37.786 --> 15:40.810
The motel is closed for business, sir.

15:42.480 --> 15:43.559
Oh, yeah?

15:43.560 --> 15:44.979
Why is that?

15:44.980 --> 15:47.360
It's an active crime scene, sir.

15:49.560 --> 15:51.729
Yeah, well, I, uh, have...

15:51.730 --> 15:54.269
business with the motel owner.

15:54.270 --> 15:56.716
I have a business meeting.
May I go up to...

15:56.717 --> 15:57.469
[clears throat]

15:57.520 --> 15:59.110
What's in the bag, sir?

16:04.361 --> 16:05.979
It's a raccoon.

16:05.980 --> 16:09.190
The house is an active
crime scene, as well.

16:14.730 --> 16:16.479
Is he dead?

16:16.480 --> 16:18.149
What's your name, sir?

16:18.150 --> 16:20.559
<i>[solemn music]</i>

16:20.560 --> 16:21.939
[quietly] Shit.

16:21.940 --> 16:24.019
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:24.020 --> 16:26.649
- Your name, please?
- Hogan.

16:26.650 --> 16:28.149
Charles Hogan.

16:28.150 --> 16:30.899
People call me Chick.

16:30.900 --> 16:34.269
Can you just please
tell me if he's dead?

16:34.270 --> 16:35.649
He's not dead.

16:35.650 --> 16:37.439
He's no...

16:37.440 --> 16:39.339
Ha!

16:39.440 --> 16:41.229
Ha!

16:41.230 --> 16:44.059
You say you're in
business with the owner?

16:44.060 --> 16:45.649
- [thud]
- Yes.

16:45.650 --> 16:46.769
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:46.770 --> 16:50.269
[exhales] Norman.

16:50.270 --> 16:52.439
I'm bringing these animals to taxidermy.

16:52.440 --> 16:55.979
So is this a... a, uh,
murder investigation, then?

16:55.980 --> 16:58.399
I'm not allowed to
disclose that information.

16:58.400 --> 17:00.269
[grunts]

17:00.270 --> 17:03.349
Well... you wouldn't devote
so many resources

17:03.350 --> 17:05.939
if it weren't a murder investigation,
would ya?

17:05.940 --> 17:08.729
You wouldn't give a hell about who I was

17:08.730 --> 17:10.439
if it weren't a murder investigation.

17:10.440 --> 17:12.309
You don't need to say anything.

17:12.310 --> 17:13.939
You already did.

17:13.940 --> 17:17.108
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:17.109 --> 17:19.559
Damn.

17:19.560 --> 17:21.559
[engine turns over]

17:21.560 --> 17:28.440
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:34.940 --> 17:36.769
Please remove the handcuffs.

17:36.770 --> 17:39.309
- Standard procedure.
- Yeah, standard procedure

17:39.310 --> 17:41.059
would mean filing formal charges,

17:41.060 --> 17:43.979
but... I see that hasn't happened yet.

17:44.631 --> 17:46.876
Someone got you
on a fishing expedition, Billy.

17:46.911 --> 17:47.879
You could use a win.

17:47.880 --> 17:49.729
I heard the sheriff's trimming the fat.

17:49.730 --> 17:52.189
- Nice to see you, too, Julia.
- He's out in 24 hours.

17:52.190 --> 17:55.020
You might wanna walk
a little bit faster.

17:58.900 --> 18:01.230
[exhales]

18:04.060 --> 18:05.809
You two seem pretty familiar.

18:05.810 --> 18:08.769
I'm this building's
least favorite nuisance.

18:08.770 --> 18:11.399
Julia Ramos, your brother
hired me on retainer.

18:11.400 --> 18:14.269
Mm, what did Dylan tell you about me?

18:14.270 --> 18:16.059
- The bare minimum.
- Horseshit.

18:16.540 --> 18:19.589
Let's be clear... Julia.

18:19.590 --> 18:21.539
If we do this, you work for me.

18:21.540 --> 18:23.089
Now, I don't know what he told you,

18:23.090 --> 18:24.789
but I'm... guessing it's something about

18:24.790 --> 18:27.499
how I must be nuts,
how I need to be medicated,

18:27.500 --> 18:29.419
- blah, blah, blah...
- Something to that effect, yes.

18:29.420 --> 18:32.611
But if your plan is to put
me in a mental institution,

18:32.612 --> 18:35.090
you can walk right out that door.

18:37.230 --> 18:39.809
Okay.

18:39.810 --> 18:42.439
I work for you, Norman.

18:42.440 --> 18:45.689
I will proceed down whatever
path you want to pursue.

18:45.690 --> 18:46.899
- Well, I didn't do it!
- You confessed to murder,

18:46.900 --> 18:49.069
which isn't ideal for our case.

18:49.070 --> 18:50.939
Yeah, I was not on my meds.

18:50.940 --> 18:53.569
- I didn't know what I was saying.
- That can help us.

18:53.570 --> 18:58.809
We can and we will present it
as a psychotic episode, but...

18:58.810 --> 19:00.359
[sighs]

19:00.360 --> 19:03.149
You didn't just confess
to murder, Norman.

19:03.150 --> 19:05.309
You said there was a body,
and you gave them a location

19:05.310 --> 19:08.149
of where they could find that body.

19:08.150 --> 19:10.359
So they're gonna do a thorough search...

19:10.360 --> 19:12.019
and if they don't find anything,

19:12.020 --> 19:14.270
we should be fine.

19:18.570 --> 19:21.109
[sighs softly]

19:21.110 --> 19:24.189
But if there is a body...

19:24.190 --> 19:25.689
Well, then you'll need to explain

19:25.690 --> 19:28.309
why you lied about murdering that body.

19:28.310 --> 19:30.649
<i>[tense music]</i>

19:30.650 --> 19:33.439
And why would... someone...

19:33.440 --> 19:36.439
lie about something like that?

19:36.440 --> 19:40.019
Someone else would have
to have killed Sam Loomis.

19:40.020 --> 19:44.610
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:46.480 --> 19:49.479
<i>[dark music]</i>

19:49.480 --> 19:55.149
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:55.150 --> 19:56.229
[engine turns off]

19:56.230 --> 20:03.150
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:08.610 --> 20:11.569
[phone vibrating]

20:11.570 --> 20:14.359
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:14.360 --> 20:15.899
Dylan?

20:15.900 --> 20:18.189
<i>Yeah, where are you?</i>

20:18.190 --> 20:19.689
Just out for a walk.

20:19.690 --> 20:21.359
Katie and I needed some fresh air,

20:21.360 --> 20:23.609
and now one of us is
currently fast asleep.

20:23.610 --> 20:25.439
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:25.440 --> 20:28.269
I miss you guys.

20:28.270 --> 20:30.479
<i>Where are you?</i>

20:30.480 --> 20:34.109
Uh, that's why I called,
actually, I just...

20:34.110 --> 20:35.859
checked into the Kings Motel.

20:35.860 --> 20:37.569
<i>You're not staying at the house?</i>

20:37.570 --> 20:39.769
No, I can't.

20:40.517 --> 20:41.689
Uh...

20:41.690 --> 20:44.020
Look, no more secrets, okay?

20:46.520 --> 20:47.859
What's happened?

20:47.860 --> 20:49.569
<i>It's not about your mom.</i>

20:49.570 --> 20:52.229
<i>I don't know anything else about that.</i>

20:52.230 --> 20:54.980
<i>It's about Norman. He's in jail.</i>

20:59.360 --> 21:01.069
What... why?

21:01.070 --> 21:02.649
<i>He called the cops last night</i>

21:02.650 --> 21:05.069
<i>and confessed to murdering
some local guy.</i>

21:05.070 --> 21:07.729
<i>I don't know, the... the police
are at the house and the motel</i>

21:07.730 --> 21:11.769
searching for evidence, but...

21:11.770 --> 21:15.689
I just... I think
that he's really sick, Emma.

21:15.690 --> 21:17.809
I think he's confused.

21:17.810 --> 21:19.309
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:19.310 --> 21:21.269
This is all so surreal.

21:21.270 --> 21:22.609
<i>Yeah, tell me about it.</i>

21:22.610 --> 21:24.729
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:24.730 --> 21:26.769
Oh, I, uh, I had to hire him a lawyer,

21:26.770 --> 21:29.359
and she wasn't cheap, so...

21:29.360 --> 21:30.729
I'll... I'll figure something out.

21:30.730 --> 21:31.769
<i>Yeah, of course.</i>

21:31.770 --> 21:33.439
Yeah, I get it.

21:33.440 --> 21:37.069
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:37.070 --> 21:38.939
Dylan, I'm... I'm worried about you.

21:38.940 --> 21:41.109
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:41.110 --> 21:43.189
Don't be. I'm... I'm fine.

21:43.190 --> 21:45.189
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:45.190 --> 21:47.359
<i>Look, uh, I gotta go,</i>

21:47.360 --> 21:49.979
<i>but give Katie a kiss for me, okay?</i>

21:49.980 --> 21:51.359
Okay.

21:51.360 --> 21:53.439
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:53.440 --> 21:55.359
All right. Love you.

21:55.360 --> 22:02.310
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:09.480 --> 22:11.399
Playing a little, uh, fast and loose

22:11.400 --> 22:12.979
with the rules, huh, Sheriff?

22:12.980 --> 22:15.019
- Am I?
- Court's open today.

22:15.020 --> 22:16.798
Why haven't formal charges been filed?

22:16.970 --> 22:19.139
Oh, my secretary
can be slow with paperwork,

22:19.140 --> 22:22.009
but she's very thorough.

22:22.010 --> 22:24.889
Your client wanted to talk
to me about something?

22:25.639 --> 22:28.382
Yes, despite the fact that you, uh,

22:28.417 --> 22:30.219
questioned him without a lawyer present,

22:30.220 --> 22:31.799
denied him his right to his medication

22:31.800 --> 22:33.299
and are now holding him overnight

22:33.300 --> 22:35.719
on some bogus murder charge, yes.

22:35.720 --> 22:38.719
My client would like to be cooperative.

22:39.321 --> 22:40.799
Go ahead, Norman.

22:41.258 --> 22:42.469
You can stop at any point.

22:42.470 --> 22:45.969
You're under no obligation
to do this, okay?

22:45.970 --> 22:49.299
No, I... I want to.

22:49.300 --> 22:52.970
I feel terrible about all
the trouble that I've caused.

22:56.470 --> 23:00.059
The truth is, Sheriff, I...

23:00.060 --> 23:02.889
don't know where the body is.

23:02.890 --> 23:06.969
I'm... not even sure if there is a body.

23:07.946 --> 23:10.059
I'm so embarrassed
to admit this, but I...

23:10.653 --> 23:14.139
fell in love.

23:14.140 --> 23:16.139
Desperately in love with this...

23:16.140 --> 23:18.929
married woman, Madeleine Loomis.

23:18.930 --> 23:20.259
She's Sam's wife.

23:20.260 --> 23:22.886
I know who Madeleine Loomis is.

23:23.760 --> 23:27.510
Boy, was I lonely after my mother died.

23:29.510 --> 23:33.799
And Madeleine...
she reminded me so much of her.

23:33.800 --> 23:35.429
You know, she dressed like my mother.

23:35.430 --> 23:37.299
She laughed like her.

23:37.300 --> 23:40.469
It was... like they shared
the same indomitable spirit,

23:40.470 --> 23:42.929
and I was undone.

23:42.930 --> 23:45.889
<i>[dark music]</i>

23:46.148 --> 23:48.889
Um...

23:48.890 --> 23:51.889
Madeleine was...

23:51.890 --> 23:54.099
a very lonely woman too,
with good reason,

23:54.100 --> 23:57.139
because Sam was having an affair.

23:57.140 --> 23:59.559
And I know this because he would

23:59.560 --> 24:02.509
come to my motel to have his fun.

24:02.510 --> 24:04.969
Nasty. Nasty, nasty man.

24:04.970 --> 24:07.679
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:07.680 --> 24:09.929
When Madeleine found out

24:09.930 --> 24:13.577
what was happening, she...
showed up enraged.

24:13.612 --> 24:16.199
And let me tell you,
it was quite the scene, Sheriff.

24:16.234 --> 24:18.814
The mistress, she took off.

24:18.849 --> 24:21.047
Those tire marks that
you saw in the gravel...

24:21.082 --> 24:22.059
they were from her.

24:22.060 --> 24:24.389
And... Madeleine and Sam,

24:24.390 --> 24:26.259
they went off together.

24:26.260 --> 24:32.559
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:32.560 --> 24:35.679
But then... Madeleine...

24:35.680 --> 24:37.849
came back...

24:37.850 --> 24:41.059
later that night...

24:41.060 --> 24:43.299
distraught...

24:43.300 --> 24:44.429
shaking.

24:44.430 --> 24:47.009
She... seemed in shock.

24:47.010 --> 24:49.139
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:49.140 --> 24:53.179
Oh, she was terrified. She...

24:53.180 --> 24:55.299
said that she thought her life was over,

24:55.300 --> 24:58.219
that... that she could feel this
noose tightening around her neck

24:58.220 --> 24:59.759
because of what she'd done.

24:59.760 --> 25:01.799
And she...

25:01.800 --> 25:03.719
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:03.720 --> 25:06.799
She told me Sam was dead.

25:06.800 --> 25:10.009
Something about the woods, a-a-a well.

25:10.010 --> 25:14.799
And... and she just sobbed
in my arms and...

25:14.800 --> 25:16.799
then she kissed me.

25:16.800 --> 25:23.299
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:23.300 --> 25:24.719
Ah...

25:24.720 --> 25:26.219
[inhales deeply]

25:26.220 --> 25:28.559
[exhales gingerly]

25:28.560 --> 25:31.599
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:31.600 --> 25:34.969
I mean, what I felt for
Madeleine was probably a...

25:34.970 --> 25:38.759
a form of delusion.

25:38.760 --> 25:43.179
It was madness, you know?
I-I know that now, but...

25:43.180 --> 25:46.009
she was just so fragile, Sheriff.

25:46.010 --> 25:48.509
She was so vulnerable and...

25:48.510 --> 25:50.139
I suppose after my mother's death,

25:50.140 --> 25:51.889
not being able to save her,

25:51.890 --> 25:54.559
I wanted... things
to be different for Madeleine,

25:54.560 --> 25:56.639
and...

25:56.640 --> 26:00.059
and that is why I decided
to take the blame.

26:00.060 --> 26:06.970
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:09.510 --> 26:12.799
Looking back, I... [sighs]

26:12.800 --> 26:15.299
With the benefit of hindsight,
I guess...

26:15.300 --> 26:19.509
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:19.510 --> 26:24.219
I... fear I may have been
an easy target for her.

26:24.220 --> 26:28.059
[sighs] Oh, my mother did always say

26:28.060 --> 26:32.139
that I was too naive
about beautiful women.

26:32.140 --> 26:35.929
And my mother was always right.

26:35.930 --> 26:40.510
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:43.260 --> 26:46.674
I know we reached out to you earlier
about your husband's whereabouts.

26:47.268 --> 26:49.499
No one gave me any information.

26:49.914 --> 26:51.419
Why are you looking for him?

26:51.420 --> 26:54.209
We have reason to believe that...

26:54.570 --> 26:56.529
something might have happened to him.

26:57.156 --> 26:58.909
What do you mean?

26:59.251 --> 27:01.859
Are you familiar with Norman Bates?

27:01.860 --> 27:03.649
<i>[tense music]</i>

27:03.650 --> 27:05.109
Yes, but...

27:05.110 --> 27:06.779
we're friendly.

27:06.780 --> 27:10.489
Last night he called the station
and said he killed your husband.

27:10.490 --> 27:14.409
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:14.410 --> 27:17.029
We have no evidence to suggest
that your husband's dead,

27:17.030 --> 27:19.149
but he does appear to be missing.

27:19.150 --> 27:23.359
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:23.360 --> 27:27.149
I wish I had more
conclusive information, but...

27:27.150 --> 27:28.739
[soft sob]

27:28.740 --> 27:32.239
I felt an obligation to
tell you what I know.

27:32.240 --> 27:34.360
[sobbing]

27:37.280 --> 27:40.149
Madeleine, we know
nothing for sure yet, nothing.

27:40.150 --> 27:41.446
And I hate telling you this.

27:41.447 --> 27:45.699
But it's important that we're able
to ask you questions as needed.

27:45.700 --> 27:49.596
Like, do you know why Norman
would claim to have murdered Sam?

27:49.597 --> 27:52.609
I don't know.

27:52.610 --> 27:54.989
Are you sure?

27:54.990 --> 27:56.859
I've only known him for a few weeks.

27:56.860 --> 27:59.779
He... likes my store.

27:59.780 --> 28:02.819
He bought paint and...

28:02.820 --> 28:05.359
shower curtains for his motel.

28:05.360 --> 28:08.239
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:08.240 --> 28:12.029
He appears to have been
infatuated with you.

28:12.030 --> 28:16.909
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:16.910 --> 28:20.569
Is there any basis for this infatuation?

28:20.570 --> 28:24.029
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:24.030 --> 28:26.949
<i>[indistinct radio chatter]</i>

28:26.950 --> 28:28.319
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:28.320 --> 28:31.449
[footsteps approaching]

28:31.450 --> 28:34.149
<i>So, Dr. Stein,
are you suggesting the reason,</i>

28:34.150 --> 28:37.569
<i>uh, for the change in the CO2 levels</i>

28:37.570 --> 28:40.029
<i>on and around planet Earth
now are because of what?</i>

28:40.030 --> 28:41.319
<i>Overpopulation?</i>

28:41.320 --> 28:44.150
<i>[overlapping radio chatter]</i>

29:01.860 --> 29:04.779
[inhales, clears throat]

29:04.780 --> 29:07.859
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:07.860 --> 29:10.779
<i>[radio chatter continues]</i>

29:10.780 --> 29:17.700
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:31.450 --> 29:38.360
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:43.150 --> 29:44.860
[door clatters]

29:46.650 --> 29:49.279
I have news.

29:49.280 --> 29:52.199
<i>[tense music]</i>

29:52.200 --> 29:54.149
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:54.230 --> 29:56.529
Put Norman back in the
interrogation room.

29:56.530 --> 29:58.189
Well, his lawyer says
he's not talking anymore.

29:58.190 --> 30:01.729
Doesn't mean he should be comfortable.

30:01.730 --> 30:04.569
I want him to feel like
he's being watched.

30:04.570 --> 30:06.149
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:06.150 --> 30:08.529
[background chatter]

30:08.530 --> 30:11.939
<i>[police radio chatter]</i>

30:11.940 --> 30:14.899
<i>[tense music]</i>

30:14.900 --> 30:17.689
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:17.690 --> 30:19.489
[phone keys clacking]

30:19.490 --> 30:21.319
<i>[line trilling]</i>

30:21.806 --> 30:23.439
<i>Hey, it's Sam Loomis.
Leave me a message.</i>

30:23.440 --> 30:24.859
<i>I'll get right back to you.</i>

30:24.860 --> 30:26.229
You need to call me back.

30:26.230 --> 30:27.779
The police are looking for you.

30:27.780 --> 30:30.109
They said something happened.
They were...

30:30.110 --> 30:32.439
I don't know. You owe me that, please.

30:32.440 --> 30:33.489
Just...

30:33.490 --> 30:36.439
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

30:36.440 --> 30:43.360
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:51.440 --> 30:54.360
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:58.090 --> 30:59.920
[knocking on door]

31:10.670 --> 31:14.209
Sorry to disturb you so late.

31:14.210 --> 31:16.709
Uh, how'd you know I was here?

31:16.710 --> 31:19.550
Oh, it's a small town. I make friends.

31:21.960 --> 31:23.299
How's Norman?

31:23.300 --> 31:26.089
We're taking care of him.

31:26.090 --> 31:28.799
But I'm not here about your brother.

31:28.800 --> 31:30.959
We pulled two bodies

31:30.960 --> 31:33.299
out of Falls Lake a couple days ago.

31:33.300 --> 31:36.509
We just identified one
of them as Audrey Ellis.

31:36.510 --> 31:39.459
<i>[dark music]</i>

31:39.460 --> 31:40.549
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:40.550 --> 31:42.169
Are you sure?

31:42.170 --> 31:46.209
Yeah. Dental records confirmed.

31:46.210 --> 31:48.299
I-I just thought you should know.

31:48.300 --> 31:50.339
I thought...

31:50.340 --> 31:52.959
you'd wanna be the
one to tell your wife.

31:52.960 --> 31:55.089
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:55.090 --> 31:56.629
No, you just wanted to tell me first

31:56.630 --> 31:59.589
so you could gauge my reaction.

31:59.590 --> 32:01.919
I understand loyalty.

32:01.920 --> 32:05.339
I understand the instinct
to protect your brother.

32:05.340 --> 32:08.509
But I've seen family members

32:08.510 --> 32:11.249
destroyed over much less
than what you're facing now.

32:11.250 --> 32:13.379
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:13.380 --> 32:18.009
Consider... cooperating with us.

32:18.010 --> 32:21.839
I can't guarantee
it'll feel good, but...

32:21.840 --> 32:23.799
it's the right thing to do.

32:23.800 --> 32:27.049
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:27.050 --> 32:28.749
[inhales]

32:28.750 --> 32:31.299
Good night, Sheriff.

32:31.300 --> 32:38.170
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:39.880 --> 32:42.710
[wind blowing]

33:05.300 --> 33:08.209
<i>[solemn music]</i>

33:08.210 --> 33:15.170
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:28.250 --> 33:32.169
[ragged breathing]

33:32.170 --> 33:39.050
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:44.880 --> 33:47.750
[wood creaking]

33:48.880 --> 33:55.800
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:58.050 --> 33:59.379
[door thuds shut]

33:59.380 --> 34:06.300
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:12.210 --> 34:15.089
[wind howling, rattling window]

34:15.090 --> 34:22.050
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:26.840 --> 34:29.918
<i>[soft notes]</i>

34:29.920 --> 34:36.800
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:51.750 --> 34:58.630
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:06.130 --> 35:13.090
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:16.420 --> 35:23.340
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:34.300 --> 35:41.170
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:51.510 --> 35:58.380
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:12.460 --> 36:16.419
[softly] Just be patient, Norman.

36:16.420 --> 36:18.419
If this goes well, in the morning,

36:18.420 --> 36:21.419
you can come back, keep me company.

36:21.420 --> 36:24.459
[sighs softly]

36:24.460 --> 36:27.709
I don't mind admitting that I miss you.

36:27.710 --> 36:30.250
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:31.440 --> 36:34.190
<i>[Norman murmuring indistinctly]</i>

36:40.150 --> 36:43.020
<i>[murmuring continues]</i>

36:45.940 --> 36:49.059
<i>[dark music]</i>

36:49.060 --> 36:52.649
<i>[Norman continues
murmuring indistinctly]</i>

36:52.650 --> 36:57.899
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:57.900 --> 37:00.979
<i>You need any help
with the dishes, Mother?</i>

37:00.980 --> 37:05.729
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:05.730 --> 37:07.979
<i>Well, I guess it's just us for dinner.</i>

37:07.980 --> 37:10.399
[typewriter keys clacking]

37:10.400 --> 37:12.319
<i>She got hurt so many times,</i>

37:12.320 --> 37:14.689
<i>I don't mind seeing her in pain.</i>

37:14.690 --> 37:17.019
[typewriter keys clacking]

37:17.020 --> 37:20.479
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:20.480 --> 37:22.019
<i>It's harder on her.</i>

37:22.020 --> 37:23.639
[typewriter keys clacking]

37:23.650 --> 37:25.269
<i>She used to love to be around people</i>

37:25.270 --> 37:27.069
<i>but she got hurt so many times...</i>

37:27.070 --> 37:28.529
[typewriter keys clacking]

37:28.530 --> 37:29.479
<i>I don't miss seeing her in pain.</i>

37:29.480 --> 37:32.109
[typewriter keys clacking]

37:32.110 --> 37:34.649
<i>This is what's best for us. So I manage.</i>

37:34.650 --> 37:36.359
Hands up, hands up. Get 'em up!

37:36.360 --> 37:39.109
<i>[over tape recorder] Well, I hope
that my presence isn't too, you know...</i>

37:39.110 --> 37:40.269
Well, hey.

37:40.270 --> 37:42.069
<i>...disruptive.</i>

37:42.070 --> 37:44.819
You want me to turn off
this tape recorder first?

37:44.820 --> 37:46.319
<i>Well, I worried about that,
but everything's been fi...</i>

37:46.320 --> 37:47.529
[tape recorder clicks]

37:47.530 --> 37:48.939
Do I have to put my hands up?

37:48.940 --> 37:51.189
It's... stupid.

37:51.190 --> 37:53.269
What the hell you doing here?

37:53.270 --> 37:54.819
Well...

37:54.820 --> 37:56.859
it's kind of difficult to explain.

37:56.860 --> 37:58.189
Well, why don't you try?

37:58.190 --> 38:00.729
All right, well, where to begin?

38:00.730 --> 38:02.689
This looks weird.

38:02.690 --> 38:06.569
All right. Starting simple.

38:06.570 --> 38:10.109
After Norma died, Norman felt lonely.

38:10.110 --> 38:13.229
And I felt lonely after my
kid and my wife took off,

38:13.230 --> 38:15.729
so we became friends.

38:15.730 --> 38:18.179
You know, but when I say it
like that it sounds like,

38:18.214 --> 38:19.109
you know, reductive.

38:19.110 --> 38:22.248
It wasn't just a-a-a
friendship of necessity.

38:22.283 --> 38:24.649
I recognized in Norman that he...

38:24.650 --> 38:26.149
had the soul of an artist.

38:26.150 --> 38:28.479
- When I was in college...
- Chick, Chick.

38:28.950 --> 38:30.484
What are you doin' here?

38:32.040 --> 38:34.539
You want me to say that he's crazy.

38:34.540 --> 38:36.170
I wouldn't say that he's crazy.

38:36.171 --> 38:38.290
Oh, really? I would.

38:41.290 --> 38:42.501
Okay.

38:44.119 --> 38:48.369
Maybe the world...
tosses that word around too much.

38:48.370 --> 38:51.159
He killed his mother.

38:51.160 --> 38:54.000
And he loved her.

38:59.790 --> 39:02.039
So... so I'm... I'm gathering

39:02.040 --> 39:04.409
that it was probably...

39:04.410 --> 39:06.789
very hard for you to get here

39:06.790 --> 39:09.909
and that you're feelin' a little miffed
that Norman's not home.

39:09.910 --> 39:11.539
Where is he?

39:11.540 --> 39:14.659
Uh... so my sources tell me

39:14.660 --> 39:18.539
that... last night
he confessed to murder.

39:18.540 --> 39:20.039
He's in jail.

39:20.040 --> 39:22.119
So what the hell are you doin' here?

39:22.120 --> 39:23.949
I'm dancing with newborn angels,

39:23.950 --> 39:25.829
trying to catch a muse.

39:25.830 --> 39:27.739
Why don't you say it
like a normal person?

39:27.740 --> 39:29.199
[shouting] I'm writing a book!

39:29.200 --> 39:30.369
About what?

39:30.370 --> 39:31.999
[huffing]

39:32.000 --> 39:36.659
Look, I know. It sounds... bad!

39:36.660 --> 39:39.999
I wrestled with my own feelings of...
of... of exploitation,

39:40.000 --> 39:42.659
but after I got to <i>know</i> them,

39:42.660 --> 39:45.789
Norman and... and... and Norma

39:45.790 --> 39:48.039
and this beautiful, haunted old house,

39:48.040 --> 39:49.829
I felt an obligation

39:49.830 --> 39:52.119
to... to... to...

39:52.120 --> 39:54.829
record the events that
have happened here.

39:54.830 --> 39:56.999
Son of a bitch. You son... you...

39:57.000 --> 39:58.499
If you know what Norman's done,

39:58.500 --> 40:00.789
you're an accessory to murder.

40:00.790 --> 40:04.040
Says the escaped convict.

40:09.474 --> 40:11.479
So this is where he keeps them, huh?

40:13.330 --> 40:15.869
That's a little obvious.

40:15.870 --> 40:18.539
Norman's more romantic than that.

40:18.540 --> 40:19.684
Oh, yeah? Then why are you sitting here?

40:19.685 --> 40:23.789
'Cause I wanted to <i>feel</i> what she felt.

40:23.790 --> 40:25.619
What are you talkin' about?

40:25.620 --> 40:28.869
To be adored like a queen.

40:28.870 --> 40:31.739
He built this place for her.

40:31.740 --> 40:34.699
Like a mausoleum.

40:34.700 --> 40:37.539
Wh-wh-what the hell
are you talking about?

40:37.540 --> 40:39.539
<i>[solemn music]</i>

40:39.540 --> 40:42.479
He dug her up.

40:42.580 --> 40:44.579
He dug her up.

40:44.580 --> 40:51.619
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:51.620 --> 40:54.579
W-where is she now?

40:54.580 --> 40:56.579
I don't know.

40:56.580 --> 40:59.909
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:59.910 --> 41:01.869
M-must have had the
foresight to move her

41:01.870 --> 41:05.239
before the cops came and...
searched the house.

41:05.240 --> 41:06.999
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:07.000 --> 41:09.739
Lookin' at you standin' there...

41:09.740 --> 41:13.499
the sheriff, who's escaped from prison,

41:13.500 --> 41:18.239
out on a... mission
to avenge the woman he loves...

41:18.240 --> 41:20.659
from her murderous and sick son.

41:20.660 --> 41:22.039
It's like... [chuckling]

41:22.040 --> 41:24.369
It's, like, too much, man.

41:24.370 --> 41:28.739
You guys are perfectly
worthy adversaries.

41:28.740 --> 41:30.119
Perfect.

41:30.120 --> 41:32.119
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:32.120 --> 41:33.579
[chuckles]

41:33.580 --> 41:36.539
The artificiality of...
of scripted drama

41:36.540 --> 41:39.409
doesn't hold a candle to true crime.

41:39.410 --> 41:43.369
Utter surprise, without contriv...

41:43.370 --> 41:45.829
More surprise...

41:45.830 --> 41:48.199
than the brain would allow you

41:48.200 --> 41:49.619
to imagine.

41:49.620 --> 41:50.910
[gunshot]

41:52.000 --> 41:53.240
[typewriter dings]

41:56.700 --> 41:59.739
[wind howling]

41:59.740 --> 42:02.580
<i>[police radio chatter]</i>

42:08.790 --> 42:11.700
[dogs barking]

42:16.410 --> 42:19.240
<i>[police radio chatter]</i>

42:27.450 --> 42:29.700
- [dog whines]
- Come on, boy, come on.

42:36.330 --> 42:39.329
[dogs barking]

42:39.330 --> 42:42.329
<i>[ominous music]</i>

42:42.330 --> 42:49.200
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:52.620 --> 42:54.579
[car door opens]

42:54.580 --> 42:57.539
[indistinct chatter]

42:57.540 --> 43:04.540
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:13.200 --> 43:16.080
<i>♪ ♪</i>

43:21.620 --> 43:25.239
<i>[tense music]</i>

43:25.240 --> 43:26.749
[door unlatching]

43:26.790 --> 43:28.789
I told you I'd take care of it, Norman.

43:28.790 --> 43:30.169
Morning, Sheriff.

43:30.170 --> 43:31.919
I appreciate the visit,

43:31.920 --> 43:34.839
but we're not supposed
to be talking anymore.

43:34.840 --> 43:36.106
We're charging you additionally

43:36.107 --> 43:40.379
with the murders of Jim
Blackwell and Audrey Ellis.

43:40.380 --> 43:42.346
You don't need to say a thing.

43:44.170 --> 43:46.669
[door closes, latches]

43:46.670 --> 43:49.629
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

